https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Special Agent Jack Kubrick is given the assignment of finding out what happened to Machine Man after his last public appearence. https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: War Zone Part 1: Road Rage
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: The Blood Brothers battle the Road Warriors after the Warriors kill a Blood Brother named Izzy. The Warriors, working for Miss Merrick, report to her their failure and are transformed via science into inhuman cyborgs. The Warriors go on a rampage, and X-51 decides to intervene again.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Fast Lane Part 4: Back on Target

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Space Odyssey
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: This issue is text-heavy as it offers a complete retrospective of Machine Man Vol. 1 and X-51, including everyone he's met and adventures that were never shown. At the end, Aaron decides to journey into the Monolith to further his own evolution.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Against the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants
Ghost in the Shell
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Machine Man takes down the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants. As he does, he discovers he can detect mutants and instantly analyze their abilities and exploit their weaknesses. When he is damaged during the battle, he senses nanotechnology at work inside of him, rebuilding him instantly.  He is the ultimate mutant hunter, a fusion of the Master Mold, Bastion, and himself. During his last appearance before he was deactivated, he copied his essence into an nearby LMD (Life Model Decoy) who later took the name "Jack Kubrick." After defeating the Brotherhood, X-51 flies away to discover more about his new abilities and to rediscover the man in him, Aaron Stack. It is also revealed that Mystique and the Brotherhood were hired by Sebastian Shaw to go after Machine Man, for reasons known only to himself.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: X.E.R.O. Tolerance
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Machine Man (as Aaron Stack) takes some downtime on a Virgina beach, befriending a boy whose father runs a hotel there. Peter Henry Gyrich tracks down X-51 using X.E.R.O. (Xeno-Engramatic Robot Organism), the prototype of the X-model robots. Attacking X-51 on the beach forces Aaron to drop his disguise. He defeats X.E.R.O. and Gyrich, then flies off for parts unknown.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: With Friends Like These
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: X-51 goes to his former teammates the Avengers for guidance and support in understanding all the changes he has recently experienced. As he approaches the mansion, he sees Justice and Firestar- 2 young mutants who are also Avengers. His Sentinal-based, mutant-hunting and extermination program goes into effect with devastating results. Jarvis sends out a call to the current Avengers, and the Vision is the first to respond.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Fast Lane Part 1 of  4: Media Blitz!
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Spider-Man fights with Mysterio and Peter Parker argues with J. Jonah Jameson.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Circuits Maximus
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: X-51 and the Vision battle in Central Park. Leading X-51 back to Avengers Mansion, Vision traps X-51 in cyberspace, where he communicates with Aaron. Teleporting away at the last second, X-51 travels into orbit just above earth. He then converts his body into a satellite, in order to keep his mutant extermination program in check.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: A View To A Kill!
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Sebastian Shaw hires Omoto to go after X-51.  Omoto kidnaps Peter Spaulding --an old associate of X-51's-- to lure X-51 out of his satellite housing. During the battle, X-51's nanites upgrade him again, making him more than a match for the Japanese mercenary.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Fast Lane Part 2 of 4: Feel the Rush!
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Spider-Man and Mysterio continue to battle on a movie set.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Jill and Peter discuss with Aaron the only way to eliminate his Sentinel programming: to erase his hard drive, including all of his memories of his father, his past, and his friends. https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description:
OLD MAN LOGAN 
Now we know what happened fifty years ago, the day the super heroes were slaughtered. We know how Logan managed to survived. We know why WOLVERINE didnt. But thats nothing compared to what happens next, as Logan and Hawkeye reach New Babylon to deliver their mysterious cargo. But before they get theretheyll have to face their toughest challenge to date: a Venom Tyrannosaurus Rex! MARK MILLAR and STEVE MCNIVEN continue the career-defining epic that will have fans talking for years to come! Part 6 (of 8).
Parental Advisory $2.99

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Moon Knight (2006) #28
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: DOWN SOUTH PART 3 Moon Knight is in a world of trouble. After rescuing a land barons daughter from corrupt Federales, the fugitive vigilante is suddenly thrust into the crosshairs of Mexicos deadliest assassins looking to collect the bounty on the girls head. But there are other predators prowling the dark underbelly of Mexico City, and not all of them have their sights on the innocent. The Punisher has traveled down south on the trail of some Russian mobsters, and hes just stepped onto blood-soaked turf that bears the unique signature of another killer. His name is Toltec, and if youve seen him, youre dead.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Wolverine Origins (2006) #34

Parental Advisory $2.99
